com.ibm.avatar.algebra.datamodel

Class TextSetter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.avatar.algebra.datamodel.FieldSetter<String>
      • com.ibm.avatar.algebra.datamodel.TextSetter

  • public class TextSetter
extends FieldSetter<String>
    Special accessor for setting text fields. Takes in a string and performs the additional operations needed to create the auxiliary data structures behind a Text field.

    • Method Detail

      • setViewAndColumnName

        public void setViewAndColumnName(Pair<String,String> val)
        Tell this accessor to use a particular view and column name, even though the target schema is not named.

        This method is used by ApplyScalarFunc to replace the encoded view/column name with the real AQL view and column name, even though the output schema for an ApplyScalarFunc operator is a temporary intermediate schema.

        Parameters:
        val - value to use for the view and column name that is attached to each Text object set up by this accessor.

      • setVal

      • setVal

        public Text setVal(Tuple tup,
                   String str,
                   Text source,
                   int[] offsetsTable)
        Special method for setting up a derived Text; puts in place all the necessary metadata for translating offsets back to the original Text.

        Use this method when you want to construct Text objects for which you want to recover the original text, for example, using the AQL Remap() builtin function.
        Returns:
        actual Text object created
